    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>The Portfolio Media plugin allows you to implement a portfolio based gallery. This uses a portfolio media post type to manage portfolio based posts and allows users to attach media objects to them in a similar way &#8216;featured image&#8217; works. This works for image and video file formats only.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>portfolio_media.zip</code> to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Create a WordPress page and implement the [portfolio_media] shortcode.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>Can I have multiple different portfolio galleries</h4>\n<p>\n<p>This is not supported</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.1</h4>\n<p>Bug Fixes</p>\n<h4>1.0</h4>\n<p>Release</p>\n"
